Sure! Here is the code for the `Solution` class as seen in the image:

```java
class Solution {
    public String removeDuplicates(String S) {
        char[] stack = new char[S.length()];
        int i = 0;

        for(int j = 0; j < S.length(); j++) {
            char current_char = S.charAt(j);
            if (i > 0 && stack[i - 1] == current_char) {
                i--;
            } else {
                stack[i] = current_char;
                i++;
            }
        }

        return new String(stack, 0, i);
    }
}
```

This implementation uses a stack to remove all adjacent duplicates in a string.
